Appendix E – Battery Pack Mechanical Design and Cell Configuration

E.1 Primary Cell Configuration – 4680 Cylindrical (NMC811)

· Dimensions: ø46 mm × 80 mm.
· Capacity: 18 Ah, energy 66.6 Wh (3.7 V nominal).
· Configuration: 96s6p → 576 cells.
· Usable energy: 38.4 kWh (80 % DOD from 48 kWh nominal).
· Mass (cells only): 576 × 0.070 kg = 40.3 kg.
· Busbars: Copper, 2 mm thick, laser‑welded.
· Cell holders: Injection‑moulded polycarbonate/ABS, 20 % glass fibre.
· Compression pads: Silicone foam, 2 mm, accommodate swelling.

Structural pack – CFRP variant:

· Upper skin: CFRP [0/90/±45]ₛ, 2.0 mm, bonded to peripheral frame.
· Lower skin: Al 6061‑T6, 2.0 mm, with bonded 1.5 mm CFRP shield.
· Side walls: Al extrusion 6061‑T6, 2.5 mm.
· Internal cross‑members: Al extrusion 6061‑T6, 3.0 mm, spaced 150 mm.
· Mass: 240 kg (including cells, structure, fluid, BMS).

Non‑structural pack – Aluminium tray variant:

· Top cover: Al 6061‑T6, 2.0 mm, removable (screwed).
· Bottom tray: Al 6061‑T6, 2.5 mm, TIG‑welded perimeter frame.
· Internal bracing: Al 6061‑T6, 2.0 mm sheet, formed.
· Mass: 265 kg.
· Bending stiffness: 10 kN/mm (vs. 12 kN/mm for CFRP).

E.2 Alternative Chemistry – LFP Prismatic (108s1p)

· Cell dimensions: 905 mm × 118 mm × 13.5 mm (custom).
· Capacity: 110 Ah, energy 352 Wh (3.2 V nominal).
· Configuration: 108s1p → 108 cells.
· Usable energy: 38.0 kWh (80 % DOD from 47.5 kWh nominal).
· Mass (cells only): 108 × 1.2 kg = 130 kg.
· Voltage range: 313–378 V (nominal 346 V).
· BMS calibration different; mechanical interface identical.

E.3 Structural Interface Details

· M12 steel inserts (12 pcs): Class 10.9, bonded with epoxy and mechanically staked. Grid: 200 mm lateral × 150 mm longitudinal.
· Shear bosses: ø20 mm, height 5 mm, machined from CFRP or bonded Al ring. Surface roughness Ra 3.2.
· Adhesive bonding area: 64 000 mm² per chassis component; defined by boundary bead geometry.

