Appendix M – Tolerances and Manufacturing Specifications

M.1 Casting (Track A)

· Datum targets: defined on suspension pick‑ups and motor mounts.
· Machined surfaces: ±0.1 mm.
· As‑cast wall thickness: ±0.3 mm.
· Shear pin holes: ±0.05 mm, reamed.
· Flatness of bonding flange: 0.2 mm over 200 mm.

M.2 Extrusion (Track B)

· Cut length: ±0.5 mm.
· Squareness: 0.1 mm per 100 mm.
· Hole patterns: ±0.2 mm.
· Twist: ≤ 0.5° per metre.

M.3 Battery Pack

· Mating surface flatness (upper skin): 0.2 mm over 1400 mm.
· Insert perpendicularity: 0.1 mm.
· Bond line thickness (adhesive): 0.5 ± 0.2 mm.
· Torque for M12 bolts: 80 ± 5 Nm (dry).

---

Appendix N – Open Issues & Known Weaknesses

The following aspects are not addressed in this theoretical specification and require further development or physical validation:

1. Thermal runaway propagation: Immersion cooling may mitigate, but no quantitative model or test data exists. Cell‑to‑cell barriers not specified.
2. Adhesive long‑term durability: No accelerated aging data for bonded joints in hot/humid/salt environments. Safety factor 2.0 may be insufficient for 15‑year life.
3. NVH / ride comfort: No targets or tuning guidelines for suspension bushings, damper curves, or structural modes.
4. Fatigue life of LPBF nodes: AlSi10Mg has limited fatigue data; for road vehicles, sand‑cast nodes are strongly recommended.
5. Insurance classification (Track A): Multi‑piece castings improve repairability, but repair procedures and sectioning lines are not yet defined.
6. Corrosion protection: Dissimilar materials (CFRP/Al/steel) require galvanic isolation; not detailed.
7. EMC/EMI: Zonal Ethernet backbone may be susceptible; no shielding requirements or test levels specified.
8. Homologation: No mapping to specific regulatory tests (ECE R100, R94, R95, etc.). L7e compliance is claimed only with additional crash structures.

These items are priorities for v1.0 validation.

